<title>CROATIA: Croatian March unemployment rises to 16.7 pct.</title>
<headline>Croatian March unemployment rises to 16.7 pct.</headline>
<dateline>ZAGREB 1997-04-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The State Statistics Bureau issued the following unemployment details.</p>
<p> CROATIA UNEMPLOYMENT	  MARCH     FEBRUARY     MAR '96</p>
<p> Total unemployed	     284,611     279,169     264,124</p>
<p> Unemployment rate (pct)     16.7	  16.5	  18.5</p>
<p>NOTES -- The unemployment rate fell to under 16 percent in September 1996, after total workforce figure was revised up to include army, police and farmers. But unemployment has risen steadily since then. Jobless in Serb-held Eastern Slavonia region are not included in the data.</p>
<p>-- Kolumbina Bencevic, Zagreb Newsroom, 385-1-4557075</p>
